<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-06 00:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Kids Dead in N.C. Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KENLY, N.C. (AP) -- A sport-utility vehicle pulled into the path
of a utility truck hauling a small bulldozer on Wednesday, killing
four children, including a 3-year-old girl, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The 2:30 p.m. accident in rural Johnston County also injured
four motorists, one of them seriously.
</P>
<P>
   The SUV's ''driver failed to stop at the stop sign, or, at a
bare minimum, failed to yield the right of way,'' State Highway
Patrol Sgt. Wade Bulloch said. An investigation was continuing.
</P>
<P>
   The driver, Christy Sullivan, 28, of Zebulon, lost her
12-year-old son and 9-year-old daughter, the 3-year-old child of a
friend she was babysitting, and an 8-year-old relative.
</P>
<P>
   Sullivan was listed in serious condition Wednesday, while a
12-year-old who also rode in the front seat of her SUV was in fair
condition.
</P>
<P>
   The truck carried two adults who worked for a power line
contractor, Bulloch said. They were treated for minor injuries at a
hospital and released.
</P>
</TEXT>
