<HEADLINE> Avalanche 3, Oilers 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EDMONTON, Alberta (AP) -- Milan Hejduk, Dave Andreychuk and Alex
Tanguay scored goals Wednesday night and the Colorado Avalanche
extended their winning streak to six games with a 3-2 victory over
the Edmonton Oilers.
</P>
<P>
   The Avalanche, which leads the Northwest Division with 94 points
and ranks third in the Northwest Division, also got two assists
from Joe Sakic.
</P>
<P>
   Edmonton finished 18-14-9 at home. The Oilers, seventh in the
conference with 84 points, close out the regular season at
Vancouver on Friday and at Calgary on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Colorado took a 2-1 lead at 1:38 of the second period when
Hejduk tucked home Adam Foote's pass while on a power play. The
goal was Hejduk's 34th of the year, and his 13th on the power play.
</P>
<P>
   Andreychuk scored his 20th goal of the season seven minutes
later to put the Avalanche up 3-1.
</P>
<P>
   Edmonton forward Rem Murray got the Oilers on the scoreboard
when he beat Avalanche goalie Marc Denis at 8:26 of the first
period.
</P>
<P>
   The Oilers added their second goal at 7:31 of the third when
Roman Hamrlik banked a shot in off Denis's stick, which had fallen
to the ice.
</P>
<P>
   Tanguay scored at 5:35 of the first period when he beat Tommy
Salo.
</P>
<P>
   Edmonton called up goaltender Mike Minard from the AHL's
Hamilton Bulldogs on Wednesday after backup Bill Ranford suffered a
hamstring strain in the morning skate. Minard was 16-12-5 with a
3.08 goals-against average and a save percentage of .904.
</P>
</TEXT>
