<HEADLINE> CBS Renews Eight Series  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- CBS is renewing five of its dramas and three
comedies for the 2000-2001 season, the network announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Receiving full 24-episode orders are Monday comedies ''Everybody
Loves Raymond,'' ''The King of Queens'' and ''Becker,'' as well as
Tuesday dramas ''JAG'' and ''Judging Amy.''
</P>
<P>
   Also returning are veteran series ''Touched By an Angel,''
''Nash Bridges'' and, headed into its ninth season, ''Walker, Texas
Ranger.''
</P>
<P>
   The CBS vote of confidence applies to just one freshman show,
''Judging Amy,'' which emerged as the season's top-rated new drama.
</P>
<P>
   Among current series with their fate undecided is another
freshman drama, the eerie, critically acclaimed ''Now and Again.''
</P>
<P>
   So far this season, CBS is in a near-tie with NBC for second
place in household ratings, with ABC on top. The full 2000-01
schedule for CBS and other broadcast networks will be announced
next month.
</P>
</TEXT>
